Step 1: Create the required Python Script (if Lambda Function is of Python)

import json

def lambda_handler(event, context):
    return {
        'statusCode': 200,
        'body': 'Welcome to KKE AWS Labs!'
    }



Step 2: Zip the Script

zip <zip file name>.zip <python script name>.py



Step 3: Know the AWS Account ID

aws sts get-caller-identity \
    --query "Account" \
    --output text



Step 3: Create the Lambda Function (Use the zipped file to create the Lambda function named datacenter-lambda-cli with Python runtime and the IAM role lambda_execution_role)

aws lambda create-function \
    --function-name <Lambda Function Name> \
    --runtime <specify runtime such as python, nodejs, etc> \
    --role arn:aws:iam::<your-account-id>:role/<iam-lambda_execution_role> \
    --handler lambda_function.lambda_handler \
    --zip-file fileb://<zip file name>.zip



Step 4: Verify the Function:

aws lambda get-function \
    --function-name datacenter-lambda-cli



Step 5: Test the Lambda Function:

aws lambda invoke \
    --function-name <Lambda-function-name>  \
    --payload '{}' \
    output.json

